<body class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Privacy Policy — Beach InSight</h1>
        <p class="mb-6">Last updated: April 26, 2026</p>
        <p class="mb-4">Effective date: April 26, 2026</p>
        <p class="mb-4">This Privacy Policy explains how a personal project developer ("we", "us", "our") handles information in connection with the [App Name] iOS app (the "App"). By using the App you agree to the practices described below.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Information we do not collect</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We do not collect, store, or process personal data (including name, email, payment card details, device identifiers, location, contacts, photos, messages, or health data).</p>
        <p class="mb-4">We do not perform analytics, crash reporting, advertising, or any third-party tracking.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">All features that do not require a subscription can be used locally on your device without sending data to us.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Subscriptions and payments</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Subscriptions are handled exclusively through Apple's in-app purchase system. We do not receive or process your payment information; Apple manages billing, receipts, refunds, and related data. For payment questions or refunds, please contact Apple Support.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Account, authentication, and user content</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">The App does not require account creation.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">The App does not upload, store, or share any user-generated content to our servers.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Data sharing and third parties</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We do not share data with third parties because we do not collect or store any data.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">The App does not include third-party SDKs, analytics, advertising networks, or crash reporters.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Data storage and retention</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We do not store user data on servers. Any data created or stored by the App remains only on your device.</p>
        <p class="mb-4">If you delete the App from your device, local data will be removed according to iOS behavior for app removal.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Children's privacy</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">The App is not intended for children under 13 and does not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">International transfers</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Not applicable — no data is collected or transferred.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Security</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Because we do not receive or store data, we do not transmit user data to protect. Standard iOS platform security applies to local data stored on your device. You are responsible for device-level security (passcodes, backups, etc.).</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Your rights and choices</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">Since we do not collect personal data, there are no account data export or deletion procedures to request. For subscription management and cancellation, manage or cancel your subscription through your Apple ID subscriptions settings.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">We may update this Privacy Policy. Material changes will be posted in the App and the policy's "Last updated" date will be revised. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

